Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.56,0:01:45.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,Chairman of the U.S. Federal Reserve Board (FRB)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.22,0:01:45.81,Default,,0,0,80,,FRB Chairman...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.50,0:01:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,People say with this man's every move, \Nthe world's money start moving, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.79,0:01:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Just fishing so leisurely...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.36,0:01:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The catch today - two large Rainbowfishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.53,0:02:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fishing enthusiast seemed in high spirits \Nand went to bed a little while ago. {no clue why he suddenly switched to some fisherman, might be meaning chaiman again but why'd call him a fisher then?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.04,0:02:05.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,Tokyo, August 31, 1985 {東京 1985年8月31日}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.90,0:02:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. No abnormalities for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.62,0:02:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job. But the overall situation \Nis rather complicated these days. {difficult; complex; tricky; delicate (situation, position, etc.); close (e.g. decision)}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.06,0:02:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take your eyes off him, ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.36,0:02:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, goodnight for now, Birdwatcher. {no clue if that's a position or a name or what's the underlying reference here, but at any rate birdwatcher is that bearded shaded guy spying on chairman}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.76,0:02:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Among companies comprising the Taihei Group, \Nas well as small banks and insurance agencies { to medium sized}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.56,0:02:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there exist a dire demand for a precise advice \Non the future development of the currency market. {actually "kawase" is just a general word for "exchange [rate]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.13,0:02:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the time being, I'm thinking of creating \Na currency market consulting subdivision. {actually just "I'm thinking about ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.69,0:02:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask Matsumoto to become the project team chief. \NYou can organize the team entirely to your liking. {entrusting (everything to); leaving (a matter) entirely with}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.82,0:02:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.14,0:02:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Will this really turn out well?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.64,0:02:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Predicting stock prices \Nis a breeze compared to the currency market.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.83,0:02:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a metric ton of factors that you gotta see through.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.55,0:02:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just being a math prodigy would get you nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.58,0:02:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, the flair for collecting data{lit is "power of information" but I've no clue} \Nand rich imagination are your only friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.43,0:02:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're yet to find out whether or not \NMatsumoto possesses any of those qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.61,0:03:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm looking forward to seeing what \Na Harvard Business School alumni's got in stock for us. {let's see what you've got; show me what you've got}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.74,0:03:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.64,0:03:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,With your encouragement, I'm ready to accept the fight. {lit is something like "fight is to well (up); to gush out (of water); to spring out; to surge" but I've heard this expression before}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:17.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,Business Headquarters Conference Room
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.40,0:03:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you don't mind me \Ngetting straight to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.33,0:03:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Companies comprising the Group, as well as a few individual members were offered a newsletter for internal business use.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.99,0:03:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Alternatively, they were offered \Na customer advice service on a case-by-case basis. {...that is my idea/what I think we should do - no clue what's mei in there} {unsure if customer is applicable to companies}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.50,0:03:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie, do you have the data \Non the applications for membership? {/subscription}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.48,0:03:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.34,0:03:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite the newsletter subscription \Ncosting 10,000,000 yen annually,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.73,0:03:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the quota of 30 companies had already been filled.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.43,0:03:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, quite a few businesses expressed a wish \Nto receive case-by-case consulting services.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.14,0:03:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so the demand was {\i1}that{\i0} dire? {no clue what's this kane, hardly "money" but could be "interrogative sentence-ending particle expressing doubt"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.65,0:03:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Considering the money our customers paid for this, \Nwe have to supply them with data of corresponding quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.61,0:04:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, the slipshod stuff \Ncirculating on the streets won't do. {to be accepted (e.g. of a way of thinking); to work (of an excuse, trick, etc.); to hold true (e.g. of a theory); to apply; to be valid; to pass (for); to do well; to get by}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.01,0:04:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.11,0:04:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to adopt a method for gathering Intel \Nthat is profound, covert and advanced all at the same time. {lit: information collecting has to be done deep, quiet and preceding; coming before; being ahead (e.g. of the times); occurring first; happening prior}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.77,0:04:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.90,0:04:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,For Intel, particularly that concerning the market,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.83,0:04:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the less people have access to them, \Nthe more they gain in added value.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.34,0:04:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's something everyone around knows, \Nyou can no longer really call it an "Intel," can you? {that's why I chose this word, "intel"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.44,0:04:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.83,0:04:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't we divide the areas of responsibility? {lit: let's decide who's in charge of what}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.45,0:04:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I'd like Manager Mikawa to find out what line \NMinistry of Finance and Bank of Japan authorities adhere to. {no clue what she means, just says "authorities; relevant authorities; authorities concerned line" - assumed "agenda/line of behavior" but could be anything, could not even be line and "tokyo kurai" instead; could even be she means "bug on the phone line"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.43,0:04:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda will be in charge of work with our clients, \Nparticularly - specialized currency trading institutions. {I hope she means this by "cover"} {actually "banks" but that's kinda contradicts the function of bank; also unsure what to make of "speciality; specialty; subject of study; expert; area of expertise"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.58,0:04:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.73,0:04:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Date will connect to the operational network of our dealing room, so as to directly monitor the currency market. {lit is "pull the line/draw a circuit" so I think she means literally getting a direct phone connection}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.20,0:04:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As for myself, with Yukie as my personal assistant,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be in charge of monitoring \Nthe Market Circles of the foreign markets, {VERY unsure about this suji thing, presumably 市場筋 - found it used as "primary demand sources" but that won't make much sense here and after; likely "source (of information, etc.); circle; channel/well-informed person (in a transaction)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.20,0:04:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,starting with FRB and the American Ministry of Finance, \Nto New York, London, Zurich, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.95,0:05:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ministry of Finance and Bank of Japan? \NQuite the challenging assignment. {/formidable enemy}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.01,0:05:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's particularly important that you keep a close eye \Non Ministry of Finance Secretary's every move. {lit is "finance official" but I've no clue what it means}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.71,0:05:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Secretary?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.20,0:05:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because he is closely acquainted to the FRB Chairman,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.17,0:05:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and there exist a strong sentiment \Nof mutual admiration between the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.98,0:05:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If they come up with something, \Nthey'll start deviating from this line. {again, could as well be literal phone line}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but what exactly is FRB?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.97,0:05:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.99,0:05:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you manage to get into \Nthe Business Headquarters without knowing even that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.58,0:05:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.58,0:05:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,FRB is an abbreviation, standing for "Federal Reserve Board" \Nof the U.S., also commonly known as just "the Fed."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:46.70,Default,,0,0,100,,It acts as the highest financial regulatory organ in the U.S., \Ndeciding on the monetary policies and supervising banks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.70,0:05:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's the same thing as Bank of Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.54,0:05:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess you could say so. But the effect it has on the world stands in no comparison to that of the Bank of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.58,0:05:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at the first picture in the file.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.23,0:06:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is their Chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.94,0:06:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,People say with this man's every move, \Nthe world's money start moving, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.97,0:06:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.22,0:06:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,May I add, Sawako sure signed up \Nfor one complicated assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.87,0:06:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's what makes her so amazing, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.80,0:06:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is currency market really that complicated? {could as well be "important"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.50,0:06:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The foreign trade turnover is $3 trillion a year. {not really sure what ot make of "fee; charge; rate"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.75,0:06:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But the currency exchange turnover in this term alone \Namounts to $40 trillion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.09,0:06:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,$40 trillion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.84,0:06:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike in previous days,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.47,0:06:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when the exchange rate was determined mainly \Nby the current balance of foreign trade,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.84,0:06:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,nowadays, even if the marked is still somewhat tied \Nto crude oil price fluctuations,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.59,0:06:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there are also interest rates, price index, GNP, \Nand even policy interventions that may all affect the market,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.52,0:06:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,rendering it extremely unpredictable\Neven for savvy currency dealers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.10,0:06:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's all about being an expert? \NSeems like I won't be of much help at all... {specialist; expert; professional; authority; pundit}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.58,0:06:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like you to be whiny about your shortcomings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.36,0:06:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.10,0:06:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an acquaintance of mine \Nworking in the Dealing Room of the Taihei Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.75,0:07:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like a tour after this? {inspection; study by observation; field trip; tour; review}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.12,0:07:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you'll learn a lot by observing \Nthe currency market operation from the forefront. {to serve as a reference; to provide useful information; to be helpful; to be informative; to be instructive}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.61,0:07:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.80,0:07:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you also let me keep you company.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawako?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.29,0:07:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how did I know you'd try to escape to here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.92,0:07:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.58,0:07:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, what you've been discussing just now - I also want \Nto know the currency exchange bank's perspective on this. {/information/data from ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.11,0:07:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You should definitely let me join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.15,0:07:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.65,0:07:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we receive 10,000,000 yen a year in consulting fees,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.65,0:07:32.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,Aoba Mutual Bank {青葉相互銀行}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.66,0:07:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we make absolutely sure \Nwe don't put our clients at a disadvantage. {TLC, very unsure but hope he means "we can't afford inflicting any losses [on our clients with our consulting]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.38,0:07:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what conclusions you draw from our Intel, \Nwhat actions you undertake
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.65,0:07:42.33,Default,,0,0,85,,is defined entirely by your own investment strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.66,0:07:43.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Aoba Mutual Bank Executive Director {青葉相互銀行 専務}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:44.66,Default,,0,0,85,,That might hold true,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.66,0:07:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but in a rural bank such as ours, \Nthe proficient bond dealers are not thick on the ground. {no clue why he suddenly talks about bonds and what's the connection to the exchange stock, maybe this saiken is not "bond; debenture​" at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.65,0:07:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we see another bank \Nbuying up American government bonds, so do we.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.68,0:07:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, we've been able to do business \Nwith relatively good profits up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.67,0:08:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There exists a 5% interest rate differential \Nbetween Japan and the U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.27,0:08:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you invest the money \Ncollected from Japanese depositors in the U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.02,0:08:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make a decent profit with just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.86,0:08:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if the dollar suddenly collapses, the estimated value \Nof the actual amount of yen we have on hands will plummet, {VERY unsure about the whole sent. tbh and no clue what's this "taiken" ((practical) experience; personal experience; hands-on experience; first-hand experience); would assume "actual"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.37,0:08:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,making all the previous profits disappear into thin air. {/blowing away}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.01,0:08:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda, do you believe such a thing could really happen to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.83,0:08:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I believe such turn of events to be quite possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.04,0:08:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However, when will the dollar appreciation correction take place, {correction; revision; redressing; rectifying}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.67,0:08:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what would be the extent of ensuing compensation, \Nhow low will it eventually fall - {making up (a deficit, loss, etc.); covering; compensation; supplementation; replenishment​}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.44,0:08:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody can tell you that for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't say such callous things. \NAfter all, we all here are truly counting on you, Ueda. {/cold}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.28,0:08:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.52,0:08:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One yours! {guess. also unsure what to make of "本" in english, could be "part/piece/bit"? should probs investigate into a real stock exchange but too lazy}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Two mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.06,0:08:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it, one yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.40,0:08:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, one yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.22,0:08:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Two mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger. {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.23,0:08:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, one mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.47,0:08:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Those "One" and "Two" they're shouting are units of dollars. \N"One" means $1,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.30,0:08:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mine" means buying, "Yours" means selling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:09:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... What an amazing place! \NIt's like we're on a battlefield!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.29,0:09:04.33,Default,,0,0,85,,This place is relatively quiet right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.33,0:09:08.15,Default,,0,0,85,,As we get closer to 3:30, \Nbuying and selling becomes more and more lively.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before the closing time? {unsure it's "the point just before ...; the point of (doing); the verge (of); the eve (of)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.80,0:09:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.61,0:09:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this thing called position regulation, limiting the number of positions the bank can retain overnight. {unsure where "sonohi" goes here}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.98,0:09:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To adjust to that regulation, \Nthe banks start selling and buying assets more actively.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.22,0:09:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Position?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.43,0:09:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The banks cannot just sell dollars indefinitely, \Nneither can they buy them indefinitely. {honestly no clue what he means to say; TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.69,0:09:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The general principle is, you buy back the dollars \Nthat you sold, and you sell back dollars that you bought, {/return by ...} {doesn't make no sense by that's what he says}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,arriving to a square. In other words, the change \Nin the number of positions has to be plus-minus zero. {added because he just says "you have t odo +-0"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.78,0:09:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,However, making it a complete zero is often impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, you're allowed to carry over to the next day \Na limited amount of trading assets. {work, items, etc. carried over from earlier/overnight} {unsure what's mama to do here after katta/utta} {actually "set/fixed/prescribed limit"/"items that you selle and buy"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.96,0:09:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And what exactly is that amount?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.92,0:09:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, it's fixed on $100,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The combined turnover of transactions made here\Nusually amounts to $1 billion daily. {no clue what's this zara, could be "common practice"} {also unsure what's "in fact/in reality" to do here}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.96,0:09:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the sum you're allowed to keep overnight \Nis only a small part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These days, because of the time difference, \Nsomewhere in the world, the market always remains open.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.57,0:10:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So Tokyo's position can be succeeded by London. {hope it's "to make up for (a loss, shortage, etc.); to make amends; to compensate for"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.03,0:10:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, it allows for New York and Tokyo markets \Nto be in coordination, right? {no clue what he means by "New York's Tokyo adjustment; regulation; coordination; reconciliation; tuning; fixing; tailoring is possible"; I suspect he again says "new york closes at the same time as tokyo opens"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.28,0:10:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.99,0:10:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what a 24-hour Market System is all about. {no clue what's last word}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.57,0:10:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We, currency dealers, don't have the luxury of being able \Nto relax our nerves, neither in the day nor at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.62,0:10:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So everyone working here \Nneeds a recreational vacation once every 3 years. {very lib, lit is "in about 3 years, the body will become (physically or mentally) worn-out; exhausted"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.88,0:10:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't right... {guess, no clue what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Nakayama, in your opinion, when will \Nthe strong dollar correction take place, and in what form?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.18,0:10:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A leading question won't work on me. {to trick someone (into confirming or revealing the truth); to ask a leading question​} {idk how's that a leading, it's pretty direct}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.14,0:10:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the news. \NYou opened a currency market consulting department.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.66,0:10:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This was something you should tell me. {/I was the one wanting to ask that}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.44,0:11:00.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 16th, 1985 \N4:50 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.72,0:11:02.45,Default,,0,0,80,,Due to the strong dollar policy we've been upholding \Nand the dollar appreciation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.45,0:11:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the U.S.-manufactured goods \Nrapidly lose in international competitiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It also delivered a heavy blow to our agricultural exports.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.29,0:11:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the streets are flooded with unemployed men. {unsure why he only limits it to city, most likely means streets [of the us]}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.54,0:11:15.42,Default,,0,0,90,,Both from Japan and from Europe, \Nwe hear one voice after another, {no clue what he really means by koko ni kite, could be "up to now"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.63,0:11:17.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,U.S. Treasury Secretary {米国財務長官}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:20.38,Default,,0,0,90,,calling for abolition of our high interest rates \Nand dollar appreciation policies. {actually "converting/deviating from"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.38,0:11:23.14,Default,,0,0,90,,If this continues, our re-election is jeopardized.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.13,0:11:23.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,President of the U.S. {大統領}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.14,0:11:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The policies must be abolished. {/converting is unavoidable}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.17,0:11:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to make some decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.73,0:11:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrange a meeting with the FRB chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.15,0:11:38.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 17th, 11:20 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.15,0:11:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, the Ministry of Finance Secretary \Ndoesn't have any trips abroad in this week's schedule?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.77,0:11:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just for this week, \Nbut for the next month or so, nothing in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.17,0:11:58.32,Default,,0,0,90,,With that girl Matsumoto as its nucleus, \NTaihei have put together a "Currency Market Project Team,"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.67,0:11:55.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,Goyo Trading, Business HQ Manager's Office {五洋物産業務本部長室}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.32,0:12:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and now they scurry about in gaudy agitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.61,0:12:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We've nothing to fear so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.51,0:12:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They're merely scavenging any data \Nlower ranks of the Ministry of Finance can give them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.18,0:12:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. It's typical time of the year for companies to run about, \Npaying the import fees on their earnings in dollar. {TLC, lit is "dollar allowances for import fees" but I've no clue; also unsure hashiri here is "trying to obtain"; assumed dorateate to be something about interest rate differential, but still doesn't make no sense because it's the "dollar earnings of the import fees" and not the other way around}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.84,0:12:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's best that we also keep an eye \Non what the upper echelon is up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.92,0:12:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.94,0:12:21.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 17th, Tuesday, 1:05 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.90,0:12:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.95,0:12:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawako, it's from the U.S. A collect call.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.42,0:12:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.36,0:12:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? Matsumoto speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.81,0:12:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Birdwatcher. \NIt's midnight on my end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.21,0:12:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Fishing Enthusiast acts a little strange, \Nso I thought I should let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.95,0:12:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.47,0:12:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Every week, our Fishing Enthusiast \Ngoes on a round trip to Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.32,0:12:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So I reached out to the pilot of his charter plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.16,0:12:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out, he doesn't have anything planned \Nfor the upcoming weekend - from 21st to 22nd of September.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.32,0:13:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, when I tried to inquire with the company, \Nmanaging Fishing Enthusiast's mountain villa,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.81,0:13:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that he might not come there again this season.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.74,0:13:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At least, that's how his wife put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.08,0:13:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... So suspicious. {TLC, no clue, could be "two ways (e.g. of interpreting a word); two kinds; two types"; could be "smells [fishy]", later also used as "suspicious" so probs alright}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The river in that area only has the fishing season opened \Nuntil September 25th.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.87,0:13:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This week is his last chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.00,0:13:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unlikely that a maniac such as him would miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.00,0:13:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.76,0:13:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The long-awaited storm is finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.06,0:13:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You really didn't have to call a meeting \Nso early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I will start with the conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.75,0:13:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,For our tomorrow's newsletter:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.31,0:13:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,"Towards the end of this week,{unsure it's asu} \Na multinational group of high-ranking financial officials
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.85,0:13:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,would be very likely to come together for a meeting, \Nto discuss the currency questions."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.27,0:13:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Such would be the announcement that I came up with. {/that's what info we'll be spreading}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.70,0:13:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When putting together the fragmented info \Nthat was coming our way,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.85,0:13:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,such was the only conclusion I could potentially arrive to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.04,0:14:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.57,0:14:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither the Ministry of Finance Secretary, \Nnor Minister of Finance​
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.40,0:14:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,not even the Bank of Japan President \Nhave any plans to travel abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.39,0:14:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, in all the previous instances, \Nwhenever a currency meeting was about to be held,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.28,0:14:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,there had always been some kind of a sign beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If we would only draw conclusions from precedents, \Nwouldn't our business be ultimately pointless? {/If things were done by precedent, there would be no need for our business.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.88,0:14:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The opponent is acting with utmost care, so as not to let \Nthe Market Circles get a smell of what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.85,0:14:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey... If you plan to steer it with great swings, \Nsuch as this news,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.91,0:14:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the vessel, which is our consulting business, \Nwill turn to shipwreck in no time. {lit: "if you row with this important info ..." although not sure this is kogu}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.35,0:14:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just diving headlong without testing the waters... {being excessively cautious; knocking on a strong stone bridge before crossing it​}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.62,0:14:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Manager! In a highly volatile world that is the \Ncurrency market, which waters do you consider safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.61,0:14:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of this, I'd like to ask you \Nto tighten observation on our targets. {lit: draw a mark, later she uses that word to say "observe/spy on"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.38,0:14:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting today, attach a permanent lookout \Nto the Ministry of Finance Secretary's house. {TLC, Very unsure, lit may be "do the thing about as much as sticking/glueing to ...'s house."}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.07,0:14:54.64,Default,,0,0,90,,Ueda, I've read the newsletter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.07,0:14:54.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 19th, Thursday. 10:45 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.64,0:14:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding on to large quantities of American Government Bonds \Nwould be dangerous through this weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.85,0:15:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Taihei Group companies were only advised to do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.69,0:15:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but I really think it'd be better if you sell \Nat least half of your holdings and convert it to yens. {/what you have on hands}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.86,0:15:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh... I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.85,0:15:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust your judgment \Nand will take a chance on your company's Intel. {unsure why he says hitotsu}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.62,0:15:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But if some other Intel comes to light, \Nplease be sure to let me know immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.36,0:15:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For a small-size financial institution, \Nthis is a matter of life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.85,0:15:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.70,0:15:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For the moment, we're making every effort\Nto back up that Intel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.88,0:15:30.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 20th, Friday. 11:40 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.68,0:15:36.64,Default,,0,0,90,,Tomorrow, I'm going out for a private game of golf, so you'll have to excuse me for not meeting you in the morning. {TLC, no clue what's that asamawari/asamairi}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.35,0:15:35.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,Finance Ministry Secretary's house {大蔵省、財務官 自宅}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.64,0:15:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,With a lovely Ginza lady as your opponent, by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing golf with a Ginza hostess? Hm. A fine diversion for a man of his position. Very well. Dismissed for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.49,0:16:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy from Goyo received a dismissal already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.06,0:16:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda, let's pull out, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.43,0:16:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But Sawako told us to peer our eyes into it \Nuntil the morning. {again, "draw a mark"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.81,0:16:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm! It's been two nights already, \Nthat we had to spend in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.07,0:16:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Feel free to rest while I observe! {actually says "tonight, leave this to me" but then he looks surprised at kacho leaving the car so having to improvise}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.87,0:16:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.69,0:16:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Yuki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.45,0:16:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Provisions for the front line. {visiting soldiers at the front to provide comfort; visit to (gift for) persons hard at work as a sign of support}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.82,0:16:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,About time! {guess, I'm suspecting some analogue of itadakimasu, TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hide! {guess as well, TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.27,0:16:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Did he just pack his luggage and left? {unsure why he says "only"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.50,0:16:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.75,0:16:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best that you call Sawako now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.43,0:16:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Came back to pick up his suitcase? Roger that. \NKeep a lookout on that position. {mark again}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.22,0:17:00.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 21st, Saturday. 7:05 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.90,0:17:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Ueda's phone report,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.92,0:17:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,both Minister of Finance and the Secretary \Ngot into the car, wearing golf uniforms. {hope}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.90,0:17:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt their destination is New York, \Nvia Narita Country Golf Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wouldn't have been for a glimpse of that suitcase, \Nyou could really think they're going to play golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.46,0:17:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The only question now, \Nhow would their final agreement look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.61,0:17:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A decrease in American interest rates would be discussed \Nfirst and foremost, there's no doubting that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.30,0:17:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because American interest rates are high, every other nation \Nis concentrating its investments on the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.95,0:17:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The result is dollar appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.98,0:17:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If they manage to reach a groundbreaking agreement,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.73,0:17:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it would mean all the nations involved \Nwill try to manipulate the currency market in cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.15,0:17:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, a simultaneous intervention?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.90,0:17:57.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 22nd, Sunday. New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.03,0:18:02.95,Default,,0,0,90,,It became an impediment to many economics of the world, \Nso a correction to excessive dollar appreciation is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.95,0:18:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.S. had already stepped up \Nwith one possible countermeasure. {no clue why only one, also no clue what's this youin, neither "preparation; arrangements; provision; getting ready; laying out (e.g. a meal)" nor "main cause; primary factor" makes sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.17,0:18:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this proposal is contingent \Non the agreement and cooperation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.30,0:18:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,between the monetary authorities \Nof all countries concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.17,0:18:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The upcoming conference should become a forum \Nfor the most frank discussion of this issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.18,0:18:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the U.S. are taking it seriously this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.72,0:18:23.22,Sign,,0,0,0,,G5 conference held at New York! {G5ニューヨークで開催}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.22,0:18:24.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,US corrects high interest rate policy! {米国、高金利政策是正！}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.43,0:18:26.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,Agreement on coordinated currency market intervention in developed countries! {先進国の為替市場に協調介入合意!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.82,0:18:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before the last weekend, the Taihei Group \Nconverted half of their dollar holdings into yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.40,0:18:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you been doing all this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.86,0:18:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,General Manager, I hate to echo your words, \Nbut in all such occasions up until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.83,0:18:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,defying the currency authorities intervention was \Nthe common sense, as a lot more profitable thing to do. {TLC, no clue what  he means, assumed it's kinda a signle nation's authorities who are supposed to resist it tho again I don't see how it's possible}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.67,0:18:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think even a G5 agreement has the power \Nto reverse the dollar appreciation trend in one fell swoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.96,0:18:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean to say, you, \Nwho didn't sell the dollars last week, the Goyo Group,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.84,0:18:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,were actually holding back \Nso as not to take unnecessary risks? {/chase after}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.72,0:19:03.31,Default,,0,0,90,,Thanks for all your trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.72,0:19:04.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 23rd, Autumnal Equinox Day. 1:15 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.14,0:19:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, Chief of Taihei Bank Currency Market Nakayama \Ngot a phone call from the Bank of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.73,0:19:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He's meeting someone at 3 o'clock, \Nin front of the fountain at the Hibiya Park! {doesn't make sense that bank of japan calls like that and says "i want to meet you in the park to explain why you should help depreciate dollar" but I see no other explanation}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.73,0:19:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? The foreigners are busy at work, \Neven when it's national holiday in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, Bank of Japan is also taking it seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.47,0:19:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine, the currency market tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.57,0:19:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,will turn into a dogfight \Nbetween the speculators and the currency authorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.46,0:19:30.50,Default,,0,0,90,,Today, our Bank of Japan \Nis to proclaim an unprecedented market intervention.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.50,0:19:30.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,September 24th, Tuesday. 7:45 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.08,0:19:35.09,Default,,0,0,90,,Yesterday, in New York, the New York Federal Reserve Bank, \Ntogether with the West German Federal Reserve
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.50,0:19:34.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,Bank of Japan, Foreign Currency Division Chief {日本銀行、外国局為替課長}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.09,0:19:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,delivered on their promise \Nand put dollar-selling intervention into practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.26,0:19:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of that, \Nthe yen rose from 242 yen to 225 yen at one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, our duty is to inherit that baton \Nand solidify the ongoing trend for the yen appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.00,0:19:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the total turnover of intervention \Nexceeds the $1 billion mark, it doesn't concern us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.49,0:19:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to sell the devil out of it. {/sell until the very end}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.75,0:19:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.26,0:20:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The price is approaching 229 yen 70 sen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.27,0:20:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The dollar is put under a surprisingly strong pressure. {no clue why he says unexpectedly if dropping dollar was exactly what they aimed for, could be that by pressure he means "dollar is still rising"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.27,0:20:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The billing companies sure are having a field day after this. {TLC, NO CLUE! 請求会社あたりが決済資金用の会に出ているな - Lit: "every claim/request/billing company is going out on a meeting concerning settlement (of an account); liquidation of debts; payment funds; capital​" - what I have now is an absolute guess, the best I could stretch this to is "[because so many companies are buying dollar today], the companies doing the billing and accounting would go out to collect the settlement funds for those transactions" even if I fully understand it doesn't make no sense because the stock exchange billing doesn't work this way; the other possibility I was considering is "the companies making a claim [on the shares] are going to have internal meetings used for withdrawing/collecting settlement deposits/allowance"; could even be something like "hasty/rash companies are going to have to take a loan to use it as settlement funds"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.83,0:20:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Bank of Japan begins its first round of intervention \Nany minute now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.32,0:20:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Gone up a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's Bank of Japan. \NOnly about 10,000,000 dollars this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.51,0:20:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.63,0:20:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The yen went down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.87,0:20:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,On Sydney market that starts trading first, the dollar appreciation is also 3 yens above the New York's level. {guess, very unsure it's "san en", although }
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.40,0:20:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quickly turning into a forced hand market... {strength market\NArtificially forming a market price by repeatedly forcibly buying and selling with the power of funds . - https://www.weblio.jp/content/%E8%85%95%E5%8A%9B%E7%9B%B8%E5%A0%B4 - I don't seem to find a matching term in english}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.61,0:20:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,231 yen 20 sen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.40,0:20:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the Bank of Japan directly intervenes, \Nit's no big deal at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.66,0:20:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda, even though the G5 prediction turned out true, \Nthe dollar market price hadn't gone down one bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.46,0:20:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, I tried selling more dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.42,0:20:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But shortly after, just in time for the morning \Ntrade session closure, I bought them back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.67,0:21:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, the market is going through the stage \Nof probing into the authorities' preparedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.30,0:21:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The trend is definitely changing in the afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.05,0:21:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true? \NIs that something I can fully trust? {/can I depend/trust that}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.21,0:21:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Selling dollars is the only way now! {TLC, no clue what he means by "here's the dollar selling only way; only means/doing alone; doing single-handed; monopoly​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.35,0:21:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!{hai?} It's back to the 230 yen level!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.73,0:21:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the authorities \Nare not about to give up on sporadic injections. {TLC, no clue what he means by ""to shoot dead; to bring down (an animal); assumed "not going to stop occasionally putting new deals on the market"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.29,0:21:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of dollars bought, \Nthey keep flooding the market with selling offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.74,0:21:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, even the oil companies started selling!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.24,0:21:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They're anticipating the dollar depreciation? {lower future quotations}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.41,0:21:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! The mood has changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.87,0:21:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.35,0:21:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell more! More! Sell it all out! {sell on a large scale}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.86,0:21:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over, at 230 yen 10 sen.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.71,0:21:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yen appreciation compared to pre-weekend level \Nis at 11 yen 90 sen! {https://www.macrotrends.net/2550/dollar-yen-exchange-rate-historical-chart - might be a bit confusing to understand, but yen was 242.05 before the intervention}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.16,0:21:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you make sure to repair this damage in the future! {actually "We're going to make sure we get this loss back." but what does it mean? he's gonna fee tsugawa for that or what? could be "make sure you return this money to us with your work in the future or smt"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.48,0:21:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This new enterprise of ours took off pretty well. {lit: as new business, good performance}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.14,0:21:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, even you couldn't help \Ntaking your hat off to Matsumoto, I believe. {to concede defeat; to surrender; to take one's hat off (to someone)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.39,0:21:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.02,0:21:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This 24-hour lookout \Nover Ministry of Finance Secretary's house...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.56,0:22:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I thought that was going a bit too far at first, {TLC, no clue what's this joukyou or else dunno what he means by "I thought I was in a bit of a situation. "}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.34,0:22:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually, it turned out to be a decisive factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.86,0:22:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.82,0:22:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The total trading turnover today \Nwas over $4.7 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.41,0:22:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly one-third of those dollars \Nwere sold by the Bank of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.46,0:22:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Foreign-exchange reserves \Namount to about $27.5 billion, {Foreign-exchange reserves (also called forex reserves or FX reserves) in a strict sense are 'only' the foreign currency deposits and bonds held by central banks and monetary authorities. However, the term in popular usage commonly includes foreign exchange and gold, special drawing rights (SDRs) and International Monetary Fund (IMF) reserve positions. This broader figure is more readily available, but it is more accurately termed official international reserves or international reserves.} {I hab no idea why he suddenly talks of that btw}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.25,0:22:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,while the combined global stock trading turnover \Nadds up to $150-200 billion a day. {stocking up on; hoarding}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.96,0:22:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{in the end, }The way the system works these days, the currency's strength is defined by the whims of its market price. {not sure what she means by "to go in the direction of; to proceed toward; to proceed according to; to repair to; to betake oneself to"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.93,0:22:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's about all I can say.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.45,0:22:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The market's greatest enemy \Nis the market itself, agreed? {tlc, very unsure it's kiken (market is dangerous to market), could be kite i think (what starts at market ends at market)}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.12,0:22:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yukie, how can you know that? {TLC, absolutely no clue what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.14,0:22:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you make a monkey out of me, \Nyou do it to all Business Headquarters members! {lit is "don't make fun of me, I'm with this a one member of ..." but I have no clue what she means and why he looks shocked at everyone next}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.52,0:22:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeeh?! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.84,0:22:49.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.24,0:22:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to take advantage of Vatican's vast funds, \NTaihei Finance and Goyo Trading are working in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.20,0:22:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, one day,
